               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus letter from the Herakleopolites(?) (Heracleopolite Nome), Egypt in which a person informs Ariston strategos and nomarches, a high civil and army official in the area involved with taxation and one of the first friends of the king, of some official business</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 11.9 x 4.6 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">9 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto, except for perpendicular lines at the lower end</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 3 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">Extracted from mummy cartonnage with P.Duk.inv. 324-330 and P.Duk.inv. 332-434</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 331 was formerly P.Duk.inv. AF74 8</note>
